3 brushes and 1 technique🌀 They all make curl clumps but they come in different sizes.

The first brush is the @bouncecurl defining brush. This one is great for creating smaller curl clumps. Great if you like your volume but still want the curls to be defined.

The second brush is the @denmanbrush D3. This one is great if you want the curls to be a bit bigger and defined. 

The last one is a Boar bristle brush. This one is amazing of you want big juicy ringlets. This one gives definition over volume. You can create volume afterwards by seperating the curl clumps when they are dry. 

Which one is your favorite?

Products do not create curls. BUT they keep them hydrated, defined and give hold so they last throughout the week 🤍

Without products, I still have curly hair but it’s just more frizzy and less defined. Also, my curls won’t last for that long.. So I love to use good products. And with good I don’t mean expensive. There’s a lot of really good brands that are still really affordable 🤍
